TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {36094=Villanova University senior guard Caroline Coyer (Oak Hill, Va.) is one of 54 players invited to the 2015 USA Basketball Women's Pan American Games and World University Games team trials., 38502=The Villanova Wildcats advanced to the quarterfinal round of the WNIT with a 63-55 home win over the St. John's Red Storm in women's basketball action on Thursday, March 26. With the victory, the Wildcats improve to 22-13 on the season, while the Red Storm finishes the season at 23-11., 37564=Notes | Live Stats | Radio | Live Video |GameDay Central The Villanova Wildcats will travel to Morgantown, W.Va., on Sunday March 29, to take on the West Virginia Mountaineers in the quarterfinal round of the WNIT., 36834=Get your tickets now for the 2014-15 Women's Basketball Banquet which will be held on Friday April 10th, 36479=Wildcat senior center Emily Leer (Glenside, Pa.) has been named the Villanova Student-Athlete of the Month for March, as announced by the Office of Academic Support earlier this week., 35446=Twitter | Facebook | Instagram The Villanova women's basketball team is set to embark on a 10-day trip to Italy where they will play four contests against Italian club teams in preparation for the upcoming 2015-16 season., 34853=Villanova University senior guard Caroline Coyer (Oak Hill, Va.) is one of 12 players named to the 2015 USA Basketball Women's Pan American Games roster. Coyer was one of 51 players that took part in three days of trials at the United States Olympic Training Center in Colorado Springs, Colorado last weekend. The Pan American games are scheduled for July 16-20 in Toronto, Canada.}
